    "instruction": "Using trace.csv, restrict to trace rows whose cmdb_id is one of [\"ts-auth-service\",\"ts-order-service\",\"ts-route-service\",\"ts-train-service\",\"ts-travel-service\"]. Parse timestamps with pd.to_datetime(..., unit='s', utc=True) and use incident window start='2024-01-23 20:35:49+00:00' end='2024-01-23 21:05:49+00:00'. For each (cmdb_id, trace_name) group compute full-series p95 (use full available series). Then within the incident window compute: window_count, nonzero_error_count (count of rows where trace_name contains 'error_rate' and value > 0), earliest_nonzero_error_ts (ISO) for those; and duration_anomaly_count (for rows where trace_name contains 'duration_mean' and value >= p95), earliest_duration_anomaly_ts (ISO). Return a compact table with columns: cmdb_id, trace_name, p95, window_count, nonzero_error_count, earliest_nonzero_error_ts, duration_anomaly_count, earliest_duration_anomaly_ts. Limit rows to top 50 sorted by nonzero_error_count desc then duration_anomaly_count desc. Also return separately the subset where nonzero_error_count>0 (limit 50)."
